{"title_page": "Islamic Arabic University", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n[[File:Islamic Arabic University in Dhaka, Bangladesh.jpg|thumb]]\n'''Islamic Arabic University''' is a university in [[Mohammadpur Thana]] of [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]].\n\nThe Islamic Arabic University was authorized by passage in [[Jatiyo Sangshad|Parliament]] on 18 September 2013 of the Islamic Arabic University Bill. It will supervise all 1,500 ''fazil'' (bachelor) and ''kamil'' (master) level [[madrasa]]s in Bangladesh. Initially it will be located at the Bangladesh Madrasa Teachers' Training Institute in [[Gazipur]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Bill tabled to set up Islami Arabic University |url=http://bdnews24.com/bangladesh/2013/02/13/bill-tabled-to-set-up-islami-arabic-university1 |newspaper=bdnews24.com |date=13 February 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Law passed to modernise madrasa education |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news/law-passed-to-modernise-madrasa-education |newspaper=The Daily Star |date=19 September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Chowdhury |first=Kamran Reza |date=19 September 2013 |title=House passes Arabic university law, amends village court act |url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/law-amp-rights/2013/sep/19/house-passes-arabic-university-law-amends-village-court-act |newspaper=Dhaka Tribune}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{url|iau.edu.bd}}\n\n{{coord|23.7444|N|90.3491|E|region:BD_type:edu|display=title}}\n\n{{Public universities of Bangladesh}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Islamic universities and colleges in Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:2013 establishments in Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2013]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Dhaka]]\n\n\n{{Bangladesh-university-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n[[File:Islamic Arabic University in Dhaka, Bangladesh.jpg|thumb]]\n'''Islamic Arabic University''' is a university in [[Mohammadpur Thana